Function Reference/unregister sidebar widget « WordPress Codex
-----------

Makes a previously available widget unavailable. This is most commonly
used within a theme's functions.php to disable a widget that does not
work well in that theme's sidebar.

Usage
-----

`  <?php unregister_sidebar_widget( $id ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$id` 
:   ([*string/int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String.2Fint "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Widget ID.
    Default: *None*

Example
-------

Notes
-----

-   Uses
    [wp\_unregister\_sidebar\_widget()](/Function_Reference/wp_unregister_sidebar_widget "Function Reference/wp unregister sidebar widget")

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.2.0

Source File
-----------

`unregister_sidebar_widget()` is located in `wp-includes/widgets.php`.

